description:
&lt;p&gt;Hywel Dda Health Charities, the official charity of Hywel Dda University Health Board, is seeking to appoint a Fundraising Support Officer to provide comprehensive administrative and fundraising support to our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will play a key role in the Hywel Dda Health Charities team, supporting the Fundraising Manager and fundraising team to further develop the fundraising operations of the charity to generate significant additional income to enhance our local NHS services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be integral to the effective running of the charity’s fundraising operations and supporting a wide range of charity-led fundraising initiatives and events.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with other NHS colleagues, the ideal candidate will have a passion for fundraising, an engaging personality, excellent organisational skills and great attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For this post, Welsh language skills (level 2 of our Welsh Language Skills Matrix) are essential so that the charity can continue to offer its services in the language of choice and in accordance with the UHB’s Bilingual Skills Strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to be held on 17.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTara NickersonJob titleFundraising ManagerEmail addresstara.nickerson@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number07584 207135&lt;/p&gt;
